data.title: Z Databases
data.text:
The most frequently-used databases

DSM-V Online (Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders, 5th edition; American Psychiatric Association) This link opens in a new window

Featured

"This is the fifth edition of the American Psychiatric Association's Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders, or DSM-V."

Flipster (EBSCOhost) This link opens in a new window

Featured

Provides access to current popular magazines, including Time, Consumer Reports, People, Essence, Sports Illustrated, HGTV Magazine, and Men's Health. This resource works well on mobile devices.

NYTimes.com (The New York Times Company) (VALE) This link opens in a new window

Featured

Provides complete access to NYTimes.com, including all articles published from 1851. First-time users, please select "Create Account" to create a NYTimes.com personal account. Click this link for additional information: Access Instructions. Older issues of the newspaper may be accessed from this database by clicking the menu icon (three horizontal lines) in the top left corner, clicking "More" at the bottom of the menu, clicking "TimesMachine," typing a specific date in the "Select an Issue" box, then clicking "View in TimesMachine."

Peterson's Test and Career Prep (Gale Cengage Learning) (NJSL) This link opens in a new window

Featured

Provides a comprehensive platform to search for college and graduate schools, scholarships, practice tests, career exploration, and resume creation. The database offers practice exams for various tests, for high school through graduate school, including the ACT, AP, SAT, Praxis Subject Assessments, GMAT, GRE, LSAT, MAT, MCAT, PAT, Civil Service Exams, TOEFL, U.S. citizenship, and much more.

NOTE: Creating an account to receive personalized test and career materials and keep track of progress over time is recommended.

PrepSTEP® for Colleges and Universities (EBSCO Learning Express) This link opens in a new window

Featured

Provides tutorials, practice tests, eBooks, flashcards, and basic skills mastery for academic success, job preparation, and career advancement. The database includes skill building resources for English, math and science; college success skills tutorials; and practice tests for the Praxis Subject Assessments, GMAT®, GRE®, LSAT®, MAT®, and MCAT®. "Herramientas de aprendizaje, carrera y ciudadanía en español. Este centro ofrece a los adultos que están muy ocupados los recursos para mejorar sus habilidades básicas, ganar sus credenciales de GED® o ser ciudadano estadounidense."

NOTE: Users must create a personal account (while on campus) to save test results, tutorials, practice tests, and eBooks for future use.

Star-Ledger Collection (NewsBank) This link opens in a new window

Featured

Search more than 30 years of New Jersey history with the Newark Star-Ledger Collection. Coverage from 1989 through today, including full-text, web-only content and full color image edition.

The following databases are newly acquired or being evaluated for a future subscription.

Digital Sanborn® Maps: New Jersey (1867-1970) (ProQuest) This link opens in a new window

New

Offers a digital compilation of more than 1,000 large-scale maps depicting New Jersey cities and towns from the 1880s to the 1950s. These maps provide intricate details about each building's layout, dimensions, and height. To access the collection, click "Browse and Explore," then choose "New Jersey," "Select a city," and "Date."

GrantForward (Cazoodle Inc.) This link opens in a new window

New

GrantForward provides a comprehensive database of sponsors and funding opportunities for researchers. NOTE: New users can receive personalized grant recommendations tailored to their research interests and expertise by creating a researcher profile using their Kean.edu email address.
